recipes.name: Couscous
instructions: Brown lamb with spices
Add vegetables and water to cover
Simmer for 30 minutes
Steam couscous over stew
Add chickpeas in last 10 minutes
Serve couscous topped with stew

recipes.name: Chakhchoukha
instructions: Prepare flatbread, tear into pieces.
Brown lamb with onion, garlic, and spices.
Add tomato, chickpeas, simmer until lamb is tender.
Mix stew with bread pieces and serve.

recipes.name: Mhadjeb (Stuffed Semolina Crepes)
instructions: Prepare semolina dough, roll thin.
Cook filling of tomato, onion, peppers, and salt.
Stuff dough, fold, and cook on griddle with olive oil.

recipes.name: Rechta (Homemade Noodles with Chicken)
instructions: Prepare noodles from scratch.
Brown chicken with onion, cinnamon, and salt.
Add chickpeas, turnip, simmer until chicken is tender.
Serve stew over noodles.

recipes.name: Lham Lahlou (Sweet Lamb with Prunes)
instructions: Brown lamb in butter, add sugar, cinnamon, and salt.
Add prunes, apricots, and orange blossom water, simmer until tender and syrupy.

recipes.name: Chorba Frik (Green Wheat Soup)
instructions: Brown lamb with onion, add vegetables, chickpeas, and spices.
Add frik and water, simmer until thick and hearty.

recipes.name: Maakouda (Potato Fritters)
instructions: Boil and mash potatoes, mix with other ingredients.
Form patties, fry in oil until golden.

recipes.name: Brik (Egg Pastry)
instructions: Place filling on pastry, fold, and seal.
Fry in oil until crisp and golden.

recipes.name: Tajine Zitoun (Olive Chicken Stew)
instructions: Brown chicken with onion, carrot, and spices.
Add olives, lemon, and cilantro, simmer until chicken is tender.

recipes.name: Harira (North African Soup)
instructions: Brown lamb with onion, add vegetables, legumes, and spices.
Simmer until thick and hearty.

recipes.name: Kesra (Semolina Flatbread)
instructions: Mix semolina, oil, salt, and water to form dough.
Shape into rounds, cook on griddle until golden.

recipes.name: Baghrir (Thousand-Hole Pancakes)
instructions: Mix all ingredients, let batter rise.
Cook on one side until holes form.

recipes.name: Makroud (Date-Filled Semolina Cookies)
instructions: Mix semolina and butter, form dough.
Fill with date paste, shape and bake.

recipes.name: Kalb el Louz (Semolina Almond Cake)
instructions: Mix semolina, almonds, sugar, and butter.
Bake, soak with orange blossom syrup.

recipes.name: Derssa (Spicy Garlic Sauce)
instructions: Crush garlic, mix with spices and oil.

recipes.name: Tamina (Semolina and Honey Dessert)
instructions: Toast semolina in butter.
Mix in honey, serve warm.

recipes.name: Merguez (Spicy Lamb Sausage)
instructions: Mix lamb with spices and garlic.
Stuff into casings, grill or fry.

recipes.name: Doubara (Spicy Bean Stew)
instructions: Cook beans and chickpeas until tender.
Add tomato, garlic, and spices, simmer.

recipes.name: Mhajeb (Spicy Stuffed Flatbread)
instructions: Prepare semolina dough, roll thin.
Cook filling of tomato, onion, peppers, and salt.
Stuff dough, fold, and cook on griddle with olive oil.

recipes.name: Tlitli (Orzo Chicken Stew)
instructions: Brown chicken with onion and spices.
Add tomato, chickpeas, simmer.
Serve stew over orzo pasta.

recipes.name: Felfel Mahchi (Stuffed Peppers)
instructions: Mix beef, rice, tomato, onion, and parsley.
Stuff into peppers, bake until tender.

recipes.name: Bourek (Meat-Filled Pastry)
instructions: Cook beef with onion and spices.
Wrap in pastry, fry until golden.

recipes.name: Zlabia (Honey-Soaked Fritters)
instructions: Mix flour, yeast, sugar, and water.
Fry batter, soak in honey.

recipes.name: Berkoukes (Pearl Couscous Stew)
instructions: Brown lamb with onion and spices.
Add vegetables, chickpeas, and couscous, simmer.

recipes.name: Msemen (Layered Flatbread)
instructions: Mix flour, semolina, butter, salt, and water.
Fold and cook on griddle until golden.

recipes.name: Chakhchoukha Biskria (Torn Flatbread Stew)
instructions: Prepare flatbread, tear into pieces.
Brown lamb with onion, garlic, and spices.
Add tomato, chickpeas, simmer until lamb is tender.
Mix stew with bread pieces and serve.

recipes.name: Tajine Lahlou (Sweet Fruit Stew)
instructions: Brown lamb in butter, add sugar, cinnamon, and salt.
Add prunes, apricots, and orange blossom water, simmer until tender and syrupy.

recipes.name: Rfiss (Semolina Date Squares)
instructions: Toast semolina in butter.
Mix in dates and honey, press into pan and cut into squares.

recipes.name: Loubia (White Bean Stew)
instructions: Cook beans until tender.
Add tomato, onion, garlic, and spices, simmer.

recipes.name: Karentika (Chickpea Pie)
instructions: Mix all ingredients, pour into pan.
Bake until set and golden.

recipes.name: Boureks Annabi (Annaba-Style Bourek)
instructions: Mix tuna, egg, onion, parsley, and spices.
Wrap in pastry, fry until golden.

recipes.name: Chorba Beida (White Chicken Soup)
instructions: Cook chicken with onion, celery, and spices.
Add chickpeas, finish with egg and lemon.

recipes.name: Tajine Jelbana (Pea and Artichoke Stew)
instructions: Brown lamb with onion and spices.
Add peas, artichoke, carrot, and parsley, simmer.

recipes.name: Boulfaf (Grilled Liver Skewers)
instructions: Cut liver into cubes, season with spices.
Wrap in caul fat, skewer and grill.

recipes.name: Griwech (Honey-Coated Pastry)
instructions: Mix flour, butter, egg, sesame, and sugar.
Shape, fry, and coat with honey.

recipes.name: Mhalbi (Rice Pudding)
instructions: Cook rice in milk until soft.
Add sugar, orange blossom water, and cinnamon.

recipes.name: Tcharek (Crescent Cookies)
instructions: Mix flour, butter, sugar, and almonds.
Shape into crescents, bake, and dip in orange blossom syrup.

recipes.name: Boussou la tmessou (Powdered Sugar Cookies)
instructions: Mix flour, butter, sugar, and almonds.
Shape, bake, and roll in powdered sugar.

recipes.name: Khobz Eddar (Homemade Bread)
instructions: Mix all ingredients, knead dough.
Let rise, shape, and bake until golden.

recipes.name: Mhadjeb b'Khlii (Flatbread with Preserved Meat)
instructions: Prepare semolina dough, roll thin.
Cook filling of khlii, onion, and pepper.
Stuff dough, fold, and cook on griddle with olive oil.

recipes.name: Tajine Hlou (Sweet Tajine)
instructions: Brown lamb in butter, add sugar, cinnamon, and salt.
Add prunes, apricots, and orange blossom water, simmer until tender and syrupy.

recipes.name: Khobz Mbesses (Semolina Skillet Bread)
instructions: Mix semolina, oil, salt, and water to form dough.
Shape into rounds, cook on skillet until golden.

recipes.name: Tamina Bzima (Honey and Butter Semolina)
instructions: Toast semolina in butter.
Mix in honey, serve warm.

recipes.name: Briouat (Sweet Almond Pastry)
instructions: Mix almonds, sugar, and butter.
Wrap in pastry, fry, and coat with honey.

recipes.name: Maaqouda Batata (Potato Patties)
instructions: Boil and mash potatoes, mix with other ingredients.
Form patties, fry in oil until golden.

recipes.name: Tajine Kefta (Meatball Tagine)
instructions: Mix beef, onion, parsley, egg, and spices.
Form meatballs, cook in tomato sauce.

recipes.name: Tajine Zitoune (Chicken and Olive Tagine)
instructions: Brown chicken with onion, carrot, and spices.
Add olives, lemon, and cilantro, simmer until chicken is tender.

recipes.name: Bourak laadjine (Dough Bourek)
instructions: Cook beef with onion and spices.
Wrap in dough, fry until golden.

recipes.name: Chbah Essafra (Almond and Egg Yolk Sweets)
instructions: Mix almonds, egg yolks, sugar, and orange blossom water.
Shape and bake until set.

recipes.name: Mkhabez (Iced Almond Cookies)
instructions: Mix almonds, sugar, egg whites, and lemon zest.
Shape, bake, and ice with icing sugar.
